    "templateData": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"UTF-8\"/>\n<meta content=\"PICC Exchange\" name=\"dcterms.title\"/>\n<meta content=\"PICC Exchange template\" name=\"dcterms.description\"/>\n<meta content=\"http://www.radreport.org/template/0000187\" name=\"dcterms.identifier\"/>\n<meta content=\"en\" name=\"dcterms.language\"/>\n<meta content=\"IMAGE_REPORT_TEMPLATE\" name=\"dcterms.type\"/>\n<meta content=\"Radiological Society of North America (RSNA)\" name=\"dcterms.publisher\"/>\n<meta content=\"May be used gratis, subject to license agreement\" name=\"dcterms.rights\"/>\n<meta content=\"http://www.radreport.org/license.pdf\" name=\"dcterms.license\"/>\n<meta content=\"2012-05-29\" name=\"dcterms.date\"/>\n<meta content=\"Kahn CE Jr\" name=\"dcterms.creator\"/>\n<meta content=\"Kahn CE Jr [editor]\" name=\"dcterms.contributor\"/>\n<meta content=\"Medical College of Wisconsin (MCW)\" name=\"dcterms.contributor\"/>\n<link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" href=\"IHE_Template_Style.css\"/>\n<!-- The absolute link to the CSS file is http://www.radreport.org/html/IHE_Template_Style.css -->\n<script type=\"text/xml\">\n<!--\n<template_attributes>\n<top-level-flag>true</top-level-flag>\n<status>ACTIVE</status>\n<coding_schemes>\n <coding_scheme name=\"RadLex\" designator=\"2.16.840.1.113883.6.256\" />\n <coding_scheme name=\"SNOMEDCT\" designator=\"2.16.840.1.113883.6.96\" />\n <coding_scheme name=\"LOINC\" designator=\"2.16.840.1.113883.6.1\" />\n</coding_schemes>\n<term>\n <code meaning=\"catheter\" value=\"RID5576\" scheme=\"RadLex\">\n</term>\n<term>\n <code meaning=\"peripheral intravenous central catheter\" value=\"RID5581\" scheme=\"RadLex\">\n</term>\n<coded_content>\n<entry ORIGTXT=\"T187_8\">\n  <term>\n  <code meaning=\"Clinical information\" value=\"55752-0\" scheme=\"LOINC\">\n </term>\n</entry>\n<entry ORIGTXT=\"T187_9\">\n <term>\n  <code meaning=\"comparison\" value=\"RID28483\" scheme=\"RadLex\">\n </term>\n</entry>\n<entry ORIGTXT=\"T187_15\">\n <term>\n  <code meaning=\"impression section\" value=\"RID13170\" scheme=\"RadLex\">\n </term>\n</entry>\n</coded_content>\n</template_attributes>\n-->\n</script>\n<title>PICC Exchange</title>\n</head>\n<body>\n<section data-section-name=\"Procedure\">\n<header class=\"level1\">PICC Exchange</header>\n<p>\nAfter the procedure was explained to the patient, the patient was brought to the interventional radiology suite \nand placed supine on the exam table. The upper extremity and current PICC line were prepped and draped in usual \nsterile fashion. 1% lidocaine was used for local anesthetic.\n</p>\n</section>\n<section data-section-name=\"Clinical information\">\n<header class=\"level1\">Clinical information</header>\n<p>\n<textarea id=\"T187_8\" name=\"Clinical information\"> </textarea>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section data-section-name=\"Comparison\">\n<header class=\"level1\">Comparison</header>\n<p>\n<textarea id=\"T187_9\" name=\"Comparison\">None. </textarea>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section data-section-name=\"Findings\">\n<header class=\"level1\">Findings</header>\n<p>\nThe PICC line was pulled back approximately 20 cm and cut at a 90-degree angle. Through the remaining portion of \nthe PICC line, a Microvena wire was advanced centrally into the IVC. The remaining portion of the PICC line was \nremoved.\n</p>\n<p>\nA 5 French vascular peel-away sheath was then placed over the wire into the vein. \n</p>\n<p>\nThe new PICC line was sized to <input id=\"T187_998\" type=\"number\" name=\"PICC_line_size\" step=\"0.1\" /> cm. \nThe inner dilator and wire were removed. Through the sheath, a \n<input id=\"T187_997\" type=\"text\" name=\"PICC_line\" /> \nPICC line was placed such that the tip was at the junction of SVC and right atrium. This was confirmed with \nfluoroscopy. \n</p>\n<p>\n<label for=\"T187_999\">Catheter length:</label>\n<input type=\"number\" name=\"Catheter length\" id=\"T187_999\" /> <label for=\"T187_999\">cm.</label> \n</p>\n<p>\nThe catheter was secured in place with 3-0 nonabsorbable suture. The catheter aspirates and flushes without \ndifficulty. A sterile dressing was applied. \n</p>\n<p>\n<label for=\"T187_12\">Complications:</label>\n<input type=\"text\" id=\"T187_12\" name=\"Complications\" value=\"None. The patient tolerated the procedure well and without any immediate complications.\"/>\n</p>\n<p>\n<label for=\"T187_14\">Fluoroscopy time:</label>\n<input type=\"number\" id=\"T187_14\" name=\"Fluoroscopy time\" data-field-units=\"minutes\" min=\"\" max=\"\"/> <label for=\"T187_14\">minutes</label>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section data-section-name=\"Impression\">\n<header class=\"level1\">Impression</header>\n<p>\n<textarea id=\"T187_15\" name=\"Impression\">PICC exchange. </textarea>\n</p>\n</section>\n</body>\n</html>\n",
